Moloto Mothapo has on Wednesday resigned as the African National Congress (ANC) Parliamentary Caucus spokesperson. The Office of the ANC Chief Whip regretfully announces the resignation of Comrade Moloto Mothapo as Head of Media and Communications and Spokesperson for the ANC in Parliament. The resignation is effective from 14 February 2017,&#8221; ANC in Parliament said.He joined the ANC Parliamentary Caucus in 2005 and had served under seven different Chief Whips in Parliament.ANC s Chief Whip Jackson Mthembu thanked Mothapo for the excellent service he displayed during his tenure. Comrade Moloto has been an invaluable part of the ANC Caucus and the ANC at large. We wish him the very best in future endeavours he wishes to explore. He can rely on our support wherever the future leads him, Mthembu said.The Chief Whip&#8217;s office said they are making necessary arrangements to try and find a replacement for him adding that the office will make an appropriate announcement in due time.-Sipho Jack